1. Looping n times inside function is faster than function calls for n times
2. Apply function: (generally goes faster than for loop with function calls)

	Example:

	func <- function(x,a,n){
		return(x/a + n)
	}

	mtx <- matrix(seq(1,20,1),nrow=4)

	# sapply(matrix, function, other arguments except the one you want to loop through)
	sapply(mtx, func, a=2,n=2)
	sapply(mtx, func, x=100,n=2)

	# apply(matrix, row or column, function, other arguments except the one you want to loop through)
